Last fall_ in his introduction to Bayesian statistics class_ two of Allen Downey’s students_ juniors Erin Pierce and Ben Kahle_ decided to conduct a survival analysis on the characters in A Song of Ice and Fire—the fantasy novels on which  Game of Thrones is based.  Their research is going viral and the two were recently interviewed on  NPR All Things Considered. Check it out!

Olin College is founded on a vision to make engineering education more fun and engaging through hands-on projects with real-world applications. Watch our approach to training global problem solvers in action.

Friends_ as you know at Olin we believe that engineering is a creative enterprise that begins and ends with people and their desire for a better world. We believe that we have created an extraordinary learning community that is bound by a vibrant culture of innovation and a vision to change engineering education to make it a fun_ engaging_ meaningful and a powerful experience. We are very excited about how well our new admission video demonstrates this! We invite you to view it and let us know what you think.

It was a busy weekend on campus! Spirit week concluded with a friendly Quidditch match; Greg Marra _10 returned to campus to conduct our first micro-residency and found himself on stage_ in the library with professor Rob Martello for a Q&A that touched on his work at Facebook_ fond memories of his time at Olin as well what he_s reading now; and on Saturday Stay Late and Create (SLAC) hosted its first SLACfest -- a design_ creativity_ and making marathon -- which tackled projects like Mobile Robotics_ Olin Connections_ Cardboard Table Design and much more.

The winner of our _Best Charlie Nolan_ contest has been announced. Congrats to Alex Crease _16!

This is the last you_ll hear about snow from us until 2016_ but we just had to share the recent recognition our facilities team received for their outstanding snow removal efforts this year. Our facilities team is the best!  Eli Carvalho_ David Gibson and Mark Cataldo received an Aramark Gold Award in recognition of the effort_ leadership and safety roles each played during the recent historic winter. The Gold award is approved at a regional level. Way to go guys!

Next week is Spirit Week #OlinSpiritWeek and we’ve got a fun-filled week of activities lined up! Check it out and follow along on Twitter_ Instagram and the Olin Family & Alumni Relations Facebook page.  Monday: Faculty and Staff Day – Students will dress like a staff or faculty member and get bonus points for dressing like Charlie Nolan – Charlie will judge the competition in the dining hall during lunch.   Tuesday: Olin Gear Day – Show your school pride by wearing your favorite Olin shirt! Share your Olin Gear on Facebook_ Instagram and Twitter for everyone to see.   Wednesday: Pajama Day – Rock those comfy sweatpants.  Thursday: Professional Day – Dig out those fireman hats_ scrubs_ ties or space suits and represent your favorite profession.  Friday: Harry Potter Day – Participate in the Quidditch match in the afternoon.

Recent Olin grad Adela Wee _15 was recently featured in the San Marino Tribune_ her hometown newspaper. Adela has started her new job as Robotics Program Director with Ocean Alliance! She will be continuing her work on whale sputum.   Read the article below.

In addition to his “day job”_ for the past few weeks Olin  Professor Jon Adler has worn another hat – that of theater director. He has held rehearsals_ worked with student actors and_ next week_  the play will be performed as part of a centennial celebration of the Provincetown Players.   To honor its rich history_ the Empty Space Theatre at Babson College will be the site of a series of one-act plays called the “Provincetown Four.” The plays will be presented on March 9-11 in the evening and include “Constancy” by Neith Boyce_ “Lima Beans” by Alfred Kreymborf_ and “Freedom” by John Reed.  Click below for links to buy tickets as well as a piece by WBUR.

Olin alum Philip Dirkse _11 is not only the founding director of Zipper Labs_ he is also working on a side project that uses real-time_ real-world data analysis to create natural learning opportunities for schools and museums. Exhibit.io creates interactive_ educational exhibits that bridge the gap between real-world data points and online curriculum.    They are currently competing on StartGarden.com for funding and are looking for endorsements. Check them out!  http://startgarden.com/ideas/detail/exhibit.io

Today marks an important milestone in Olin’s history. Jeffrey Holzgrafe ’15_ from Austin_ TX_ was chosen to receive a Marshall Scholarship to study Physics at Cambridge University in the UK.  He becomes the first Olin student to be so honored.  The Marshall Scholarship is one of the most prestigious post-graduate fellowships available to Americans.  As described by the sponsor_ _Marshall Scholarships finance young Americans of high ability to study for a degree in the United Kingdom. Up to forty Scholars are selected each year to study at graduate level at an UK institution in any field of study._    Congratulations to Jeffrey Holtzgrafe on his incredible accomplishment and to Olin College faculty and staff who help prepare him for the intense competition that led to his selection.

We are please to share this article _Olin College is doing just fine_ in case you heard otherwise_ which appeared in the Boston Business Journal on Tuesday. It was authored by @BosBizCraig and sets the record straight on Olin_s financial stability.

Olin and Babson born startup Indico Data Solutions has been working hard on their product and practice pitches since being initiated into Techstars Boston Fall 2014 class. All of their hard work was tested this morning during the Boston Techstars Demo Day where they pitched to a room full of investors at the House of Blues in Boston. Below is the team standing in front of a bus of Olin students that showed up to cheer on their classmates!  Indico is creating “productivity tools for data scientists at small and medium businesses by uniquely automating parts of their workflow. indico is bringing tools and workflow to machine learning_ making every programmer a 10x data scientist.”  Not only did the team rock their pitches_ they also announced that they closed a $3 million seed round!   Congratulations to Oliners Slater Victoroff ‘16_ Aidan McLaughlin ‘17_ Madison May ‘17_ Alec Radford ‘16 and Ezra Varady ‘18.
